INSERT OR IGNORE INTO `lessons` (`id`,`course_id`,`title`,`section_id`,`lesson_type`,`content`,`content_format`,`video_key`,`primary_asset_id`,`intro_asset_id`,`duration_minutes`,`is_preview`,`available_after_days`,`required_watch_percent`,`transcript`,`experience_json`,`position`,`updated_at`) SELECT 'cmf-module-3-31-lesson-01','cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production','Congratulations on Completing the Crypto Mastery Digital Asset Education Pathway - Part 1','cmf-module-3-31','text','### Congratulations on Completing the Crypto Mastery Digital Asset Education Pathway - Part 1\n\nCongratulations on completing Crypto Mastery: The Complete Digital Asset Education Pathway.\n\nReaching this point represents far more than finishing a collection of lessons. You have worked through a structured learning journey that began with the foundations of money and blockchain technology and progressed into advanced market analysis, portfolio strategy, decentralised finance, institutional participation and digital asset governance.\n\nThe digital asset world is often presented through excitement, speculation and promises of rapid financial success. This programme was designed to give you something more valuable: the knowledge and analytical discipline required to think independently.\n\nYou began by learning why money exists, how it has evolved and why Bitcoin introduced a fundamentally different approach to digital ownership and value transfer. You explored how blockchains maintain shared records, how decentralisation works and how coins, tokens and digital assets differ from one another.\n\nYou also developed the practical knowledge required to participate safely. You learned how public and private keys work, how wallets protect assets and why seed phrases must be secured carefully. You examined the differences between hot and cold storage, centralised and decentralised exchanges, and the correct processes for buying, selling, sending and receiving cryptocurrency.\n\nMost importantly, you learned that personal responsibility is central to digital asset participation. Security is not an optional technical concern. It is part of every transaction, wallet, exchange and investment decision.\n\nAs you progressed, you moved beyond basic participation and began studying how digital asset markets function. You explored liquidity, volatility, market capitalisation, token supply and the economic incentives created by tokenomics.\n\nYou learned how bull markets, bear markets and periods of consolidation influence investor behaviour. You examined the psychology of fear, greed, confidence, capitulation and speculation, while recognising that markets are shaped by human decisions as much as by technology.\n\nYou developed the ability to evaluate cryptocurrency projects through their purpose, technology, teams, roadmaps, communities, adoption and network effects. You learned how to read a white paper critically rather than accepting its claims at face value.\n\nYou also studied the supply side of digital assets in greater depth. Token inflation, burns, vesting schedules, insider allocations and future unlocks all affect the relationship between demand and available supply. You now understand that a promising project can still produce a poor investment outcome when its token economics do not benefit holders.\n\nYour market-analysis skills expanded through fundamental and technical analysis. You learned how to interpret candlestick charts, support, resistance, trends, volume, liquidity and technical indicators.\n\nMore importantly, you learned that no indicator operates perfectly and no chart guarantees a future outcome. Technical analysis provides a framework for understanding market behaviour, planning entries and defining invalidation. It does not remove uncertainty.\n\nYou then entered the rapidly developing world of decentralised finance. You examined decentralised exchanges, automated market makers, liquidity pools, staking, lending and borrowing. You learned where DeFi returns come from and why a high displayed yield can conceal inflation, leverage, smart contract risk, liquidity pressure or potential loss.\n\nBy the time you reached the advanced course, you were no longer learning only how digital assets operate. You were learning how to analyse and manage them as part of a complete strategy.\n\nYou explored trend-following, mean-reversion, breakout and momentum approaches. You learned how market regimes influence strategy selection and why a method suited to one environment may perform poorly in another.\n\nYou developed a deeper understanding of futures, perpetual contracts and options. You examined leverage, margin, funding, liquidation, volatility and the options Greeks. These concepts showed how derivatives can be used for speculation, hedging and risk management, but also how quickly unmanaged leverage can destroy capital.\n\nYour understanding of blockchain data became increasingly sophisticated. You learned how to analyse network activity, wallet behaviour, holder cohorts, exchange flows, realised value and cost basis.\n\nYou studied how long-term and short-term holders behave differently, how supply moves between profit and loss and how on-chain valuation indicators can provide context across market cycles. You also learned the limitations of these models. Blockchain data records movement, but it does not reveal every person’s identity, intention or actual purchase price.\n\nYou connected digital asset markets with the wider financial system by studying monetary policy, interest rates, credit, currencies and global liquidity. You learned that digital assets may be decentralised technologically while remaining deeply connected to investor risk appetite, funding conditions and the global economy.\n\nYou examined cross-asset correlations and discovered why owning many tokens does not necessarily create genuine diversification. Several holdings may still depend on the same market trend, stablecoin, exchange, blockchain or source of liquidity.','markdown',NULL,NULL,NULL,6,0,0,0,'',NULL,1,1785297600000 WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM `courses` WHERE `id`='cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production');
--> statement-breakpoint
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO `lessons` (`id`,`course_id`,`title`,`section_id`,`lesson_type`,`content`,`content_format`,`video_key`,`primary_asset_id`,`intro_asset_id`,`duration_minutes`,`is_preview`,`available_after_days`,`required_watch_percent`,`transcript`,`experience_json`,`position`,`updated_at`) SELECT 'cmf-module-3-31-lesson-02','cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production','Congratulations on Completing the Crypto Mastery Digital Asset Education Pathway - Part 2','cmf-module-3-31','text','### Congratulations on Completing the Crypto Mastery Digital Asset Education Pathway - Part 2\n\nYour portfolio-management knowledge developed through position sizing, risk budgeting, optimisation, rebalancing, drawdown control, benchmarking and performance attribution. You learned that the quality of an asset does not determine the correct position size. Position size must be determined by the amount of loss the complete portfolio can tolerate.\n\nYou also explored the infrastructure supporting institutional participation. Custody, investment products, compliance, governance and operational resilience are essential parts of the digital asset ecosystem. A successful investment thesis can still fail when an exchange, custodian, bridge, protocol or internal approval process breaks down.\n\nPerhaps the most important lesson from this entire pathway is that successful digital asset participation is not based on predicting every market movement.\n\nIt is based on developing a repeatable process.\n\nThat process begins with understanding the asset and its economic purpose. It continues through valuation, market analysis, portfolio construction, execution and custody. It includes defining how much can be lost, what evidence supports the decision and what conditions would invalidate the original thesis.\n\nThe knowledge you have gained should help you evaluate opportunities more calmly, recognise risks earlier and avoid decisions driven entirely by excitement, fear or social pressure.\n\nIt should help you ask better questions when a new project, token, protocol or investment product appears.\n\nWhere does the return come from?\n\nWho controls the system?\n\nWhat creates demand?\n\nHow much supply may enter the market?\n\nWhich risks are hidden behind the displayed yield?\n\nWhat would happen if the market fell sharply?\n\nCan the position be exited?\n\nWhat would prove the investment thesis wrong?\n\nThese questions will remain valuable even as the technology changes.\n\nThe digital asset industry will continue evolving. New networks, applications, regulations and investment structures will emerge. Some will create genuine economic value. Others will be driven by temporary narratives, unsustainable incentives or misleading promises.\n\nCompleting this programme does not mean that there is nothing more to learn.\n\nIt means that you now possess a foundation strong enough to continue learning independently.\n\nWe hope this knowledge helps you participate in digital asset markets with greater confidence, discipline and responsibility. We hope it allows you to protect yourself from avoidable mistakes, evaluate innovation objectively and make decisions aligned with your own goals and risk tolerance.\n\nWhether you use these skills as an investor, trader, entrepreneur, adviser, professional or simply as an informed participant in the changing financial system, the principles remain the same.\n\nProtect your capital.\n\nQuestion unsupported claims.\n\nUnderstand what you own.\n\nRespect uncertainty.\n\nManage risk before pursuing return.\n\nContinue learning.\n\nCongratulations once again on completing the full Crypto Mastery digital asset education pathway.\n\nYou have moved from understanding the basic foundations of cryptocurrency to developing a complete advanced strategy framework.\n\nYou are now better equipped not merely to participate in the digital asset economy, but to approach it thoughtfully, critically and responsibly.\n\nWell done, and may the knowledge you have gained continue to serve you throughout your future learning, decisions and opportunities.','markdown',NULL,NULL,NULL,4,0,0,0,'',NULL,2,1785297600000 WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM `courses` WHERE `id`='cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production');
--> statement-breakpoint